# What I'm looking for

**Role type:** Senior Product Manager, preferably on AI/LLM products, data platforms, or developer tooling. Open to Group/Lead PM for the right team.

**Why this:** I want to work on products where the interesting problems are upstream — shaping what gets built, not just shipping someone else's backlog. AI products right now are the rare place where product, engineering, and research all meet, and the right PM can move the needle. I've been building agentic workflows for my own work (CrewAI, Claude Code plugins) and I want to do it full-time for a product with real users.

**Company stage:** Series A–C. Past seed. Not late-stage public unless the specific team is early. I prefer working at companies where the product is real but the playbook isn't written yet.

**Team:** Small enough that I can own a full area, big enough that I'm not the only PM. Strong engineering culture. Design is respected. Data is real (not vibes).

**What I bring:**
- 10+ years of product — B2B SaaS, platforms, and technical products
- Hands-on with AI/LLM tooling (CrewAI, Claude agents, prompting, evals)
- Norwegian + English, currently in Oslo
- Change management academic background (MAN5006 at BI) — useful for org-scale rollouts
- Comfortable in ambiguity, strong writing, strong stakeholder comms

**What I don't want:**
- Pure roadmap-delivery PM role with no strategy component
- Heavy agency / consulting / services work
- Gambling, weapons, ad-tech surveillance
- Sales engineering disguised as PM
